<dt style=""><a name="10-1507" style="">LEARN TO RIDE WITH STAFF FROM CAMP BIKE FUN!</a>
<a href="#10-1507"><img src="images/chain.gif" alt="Link" title="Link to this event" border="0"></a>
</dt><dd><img src="images-pp2010/1507.jpg" alt="" width="300" align="left" height="46.1538461538">
<div style="">Woodlawn School, 7200 NE 11th Ave, Portland <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=7200+NE+11th+Ave&amp;Dcty=PO&amp;by=9:45+a.m.&amp;on=06/10/10" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="images/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a> (near Woodlawn Park in NE Portland)</div>
9:45am - 11:45am<div style="">
<em>*You MUST preregister at 503-382-7285*
<br>Don't know how to ride a bike/ or you could use a little extra help?
 Staff of Camp Bike Fun are offering to teach adults how to ride today. 
This will be a fundraiser for scholarships for 10-15 year olds attending
 Camp Bike Fun this summer at the North Portland Bike Works (A two week 
long urban adventure summer field trip program)
