</dt><dd><div style="">Firefighters Memorial Park , Corner of NW 18th and Burnside <a href="http://trimet.org/go/cgi-bin/plantrip.cgi?to=Corner+of+NW+18th+and+Burnside&amp;by=10:00+a.m.&amp;on=06/15/10" target="_BLANK" title="TriMet trip planner"><img alt="Take Trimet" src="images/trimetrose.gif" border="0"></a> (Next to the Downtown Performance Bike Shop)</div>
10:00am<div style="">
<em>This economy got you down? &nbsp;Were you laid off, let go, 
separated, terminated, or just plain fired? &nbsp;Well, grab your pink 
slips, and join me on the 9 to 5 ride.
<br>
<br>Ride will be a gentle paced (Hell, we're unemployed. &nbsp;We got 
time! ) seeking fire (as in "YOU'RE FIRED") related themes (NO 
ARSON!!!). &nbsp;So, leave the poor working slobs behind as we ride 
starting around 10am (go ahead, sleep in!)
<br>
<br>Extra points for Pink Slips (Worn, or not)...
<br>Bring money for any food/drinks, and a chance at MEGABUCKS
<br>
<br>Helmets STRONGLY recommended
